SYSTEM VARIABLES
.c
------------------------------
.b3.lm20.ts5,20.i-15
SYNTAX	DESCRIPTION
.i-15
------	-----------
.b2.i-15
The following variables can be set by the user:
.b2.i-15
_.BXAUS	Automatic save indicator.  If this variable is#1 the
workspace is automatically backed up each time a function
definition is closed.
.b1.i-15
_.BXCT	Degree of tolerance or relative fuzz to be applied
in performing comparisons.  Value must be in range 0 to
approximately 1E-8.
.b1.i-15
_.BXGAG	Allow other users to communicate with your terminal.  Value of
1 means allow such action;  0 means disallow.
.b1.i-15
_.BXIO	Index origin for arrays.  Possible values are 0 or
1.
.ifnot vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXLX	Latent expression to be executed automatically when
the workspace is activated.
.endif vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXPP	Precision of non-integer numeric output.  Value must
be integer in range 1 to 18.
.b1.i-15
_.BXPW	Maximum number of characters that may appear on an
output line.  Value must be integer in range 30 to 390.
.b1.i-15
_.BXRL	Current link in the chain of random numbers
generated by the roll and deal operators.
.b1.i-15
_.BXSF	Prompt or signal message for evaluated input.
.b1.i-15
_.BXTIMELIMIT	Amount of time APL waits for user input when doing
quote-quad and quad-del input.
.ifnot vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXTRAP	Expression to be executed automatically when
an error occurs.
.endif vb
.b2.i-15
The following variables retain system specified values:
.b2.i-15
_.BXAI	Account information on the current APL session.
.b1.i-15
_.BXALPHA	Vector containing the 27 characters: .LD and
A-Z.
.b1.i-15
_.BXALPHAU	Vector containing the 27 characters: .Z@ and
_.ZA-.ZZ.
.b1.i-15
_.BXASCII	Vector containing the 128 ASCII characters:
octal 000-177.
.b1.i-15
_.BXAV	Vector of all possible characters which can be
expressed in the APL system. 
.b1.i-15
_.BXCTRL	Vector containing the 32 ASCII control
characters: octal 000-037.
.b1.i-15
_.BXERROR	Error message from last error.
.b1.i-15
_.BXLC	Vector of the line numbers in the APL workspace's
state indicator.
.b1.i-15
_.BXNUM	Vector containing the 10 digits: 0-9.
.b1.i-15
_.BXTIMEOUT	Flag indicating whether or not .BXTIMELIMIT
expired on last quad input.  Also indicates whether or not last
input from a PTY was terminated with a LF.
.b1.i-15
_.BXTS	Current date and time in base 10 format.
.b1.i-15
_.BXTT	Type of terminal being used in the current APL session.
.b1.i-15
_.BXUL	Job number associated with the current APL session
(in base 10).
.b1.i-15
_.BXWA	Returns the amount that the active workspace may increase.
