.c
------------------------------
.b3.lm20.ts5,20.i-15
SYNTAX	DESCRIPTION
.i-15
------	-----------
.b1.i-15
_.BXBREAK#A	Causes execution to terminate, suspending
the current function and entering immediate mode.
.ifnot vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXCR#A	Returns a canonical representation of the defined
function whose name is the character string A.
.endif vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXDL#S	Delays execution for S seconds.
.b1.i-15
_.BXEX#A	Erases an existing use of a name in the user's workspace.
.b1.i-15
_.BXFI#A	Parses the character vector A as a numeric vector.
.ifnot vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXFX#M	Reverses the operation performed by .BXCR.
.endif vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXNC#A	Returns the classification of one or more
names.  Values returned are 0-available for any use, 1-label
name, 2-variable name, 3-function name, 4-not available for
use as a name.
.B1.I-15
[A]#.BXNL#N[...]
.br
Constructs a list of named objects in the user's workspace.
.b1.i-15
_.BXQCO#A	Quietly Copies a workspace according to the
information in A.
.b1.i-15
_.BXQLD#A	Quietly Loads a workspace according to the information
in A.
.b1.i-15
_.BXQPC#A	Quietly Protected Copies a workspace according to the
information in A.
.ifnot vb
.b1.i-15
['TEXT'] .BXSIGNAL E
.br
Signals the error E from the current function.
.endif vb
.b1.i-15
_.BXVI#A	Validates the character vector A as a numeric vector.
.ifnot vb
.b2.i-15
The following functions are related to the file system:
.b2.i-15
A#.BXAPPEND#C,H,T
.br
Appends a data item to a /BU or /DA file.
.b1.i-15
_.BXASS '[N] [FILENAME] [PASSWORD] [/FILE-TYPE] [/SHARE] [/DUMP]'
.br
Assigns a file on the (optionally specified) channel.
Returns channel number used.
.b1.i-15
_.BXCHS#N	Returns file status on channel N.
.b1.i-15
_A#.BXCIQ#H,T	Interprets part of a logical input record
made up of different data types.
.b1.i-15
_.BXCLS#N	Closes files on one or more channels.
.b1.i-15
_A#.BXCOQ#H,T	Combines several different data types into a
single logical output record.
.b1.i-15
_.BXDAS#N	Deassigns files on one or more channels.
.b1.i-15
_.BXDEQ#N [LOCK-NUMBER] [SHARE-BIT]
.br
Synchronizes shared access to multiple-user files by releasing the locked file.
.b1.i-15
_.BXDVC#N	Returns device characteristics word and
block size for one or more channels.
.b1.i-15
_.BXENQ#N#[LOCK-NUMBER]#[SHARE-BIT]
.br
Synchronizes shared access to multiple-user files by locking
the requested file.
.b1.i-15
_.BXFCM#N	Returns component numbers and sizes for all
components in a direct access file.
.b1.i-15
_.BXFLS#N	Returns sharing status, record size, and
pointer information for one or more files.
.b1.i-15
N#.BXMTP#OPS	Performs a variety of magnetic tape operations.
.b1.i-15
N#.BXRENAME#C	Renames the file associated with channel C using the file
specification N.
